# Directories to symlink from the main worktree into new worktrees.
# One path per line, relative to project root.
# Lines starting with # are comments.
#
# When you run `grove add`, these directories are automatically
# symlinked from the main worktree, so new worktrees start with
# warm build caches instead of cold ones.
#
# Use `grove cache --status` to check symlink state.
# Use `grove cache --unlink` to remove symlinks.
# Use `grove add --no-cache` to skip symlinking for one worktree.

node_modules
# .next
# .cache
# dist
# target
